sql:
SELECT SUM(s.quantity_sold * p.price) AS total_revenue
FROM sales s
JOIN products p ON s.product_id = p.product_id;

external_knowledge:
- Net sales are calculated by subtracting the number of returns (both too small and too large) from the total quantity sold;
- Size labels represent different sizes of products (e.g., XS, S, M);
- Returns are categorized based on the reason for return, such as "too small" or "too large".

- Size adjustment factor: A metric used to adjust the fit of clothing sizes based on customer feedback and return data;
- Returns due to sizing issues: Returns where the customers indicate that the clothing was either "too small" or "too large";
- Average measurements: The mean values of various body measurements (natural waist, thigh, hip, chest, sleeve length, inseam, shoulder width) for each size.

- "shining star" refers to the product with the highest sales rank;
- "most sold item" means the product with the highest total quantity sold;
- "average price of its category" means the average price of all products in the same category as the most sold item.
